Hyatt Regency Lagos is a hospitality development that features a total of 360 rooms plus 40 suites, and 149 super luxury residences for sale, coming up within the Diplomatic Enclave of Victoria Island, on the expansive site of the former Australian High Commission at the junction of Ahmadu Bello Way and Ozumba Mbadiwe Street. Also Read: Lagos-American Specialist Hospital (LASH) Development in Lagos, Nigeria Some of the hotel amenities will include world-class restaurants, a state-of-the-art fitness center, elegant gardens, beautiful decorative fountains, and pool features as well as executive business centers, in excess of 2,000 square meters of flexible conference space and ballrooms.  Developer: Churchgate Group in partnership with Hyatt International. Main Contractor: Julius Berger Nigeria Plc Architect: DAA Architects Limited MEP Engineer: Nairda Project Manager: Gassim The Hyatt Regency Lagos will be operated by the Hyatt Resorts and Hotels Group